T1  - Some tests of the consumption-based asset pricing model
AU  - Wheatley, Simon
JO  - Journal of Monetary Economics
VL  - 22
IS  - 2
SP  - 193
EP  - 215
PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/09/01/
SN  - 0304-3932
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3932(88)90019-0
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304393288900190
AB  - This paper tests a simple version of the consumption-based asset pricing model. Simulations show that when consumption is measured with error tests of the model's restrictions on the serial dependence of a vector of asset returns and consumption growth can be biased towards rejection. These simulations also reveal that, whether or not consumption is measured with error, estimates of a representative individual's relative risk aversion, computed under these restrictions, can be biased downwards substantially in finite samples. Tests of the model's restrictions on the marginal means of a cross-section of returns cannot reject it.
ER  - 
